<H3> <TI>   Iranian Press Agency Cited on Mojahedin in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20275A Belgrade POLlTlKA in Serbo-Croatian 5 Jan 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> 94P20275A </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade POLlTlKA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Public Admission by Iran on Presence </F>
of Mojahedin in Bosnia"] 
  [Text] The Iranian press agency IRNA has reported that two 
mojahedin fighting against Serbian forces have died on the 
Bosnian battlefield. According to the agency, it is a question 
of two Arabs -- Habib Al Madani and Abdulah al Saleh. IRNA does 
not specify from which Arab country the two mojahedin came. 
  The news from the Iranian news agency would not draw special 
attention, considering the tragic fact that people are dying on 
the Bosnian battlefield every day. However, for the first time 
since the beginning of the Bosnian civil war, media of the 
Islamic world have admitted that mojahedin from Islamic 
countries have also been fighting on the side of the Bosnian 
Muslims. 
  IRNA also states that "a certain number of Arabs have been 
working" in the former Bosnia-Herzegovina in the area of the 
"humanitarian aid and education." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-40243 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "jpeer004__s94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   JPRS-EER-94-004-S </AU>
